# SHAKE256(0^33) 256-byte squeeze, run AFTER a SHA3-512 op (mode switch).
# Reference is the clean shake_256(0^33) output (same as shake_squeeze_test).
# If w0 matches but w4/w5/w7 differ, the SHA3->SHAKE256 switch corrupts the
# second SHAKE256 block -- the block f8 reads and cbd2 does not.
